# AKOS UX Discipline

Use this rule whenever authoring or reviewing **component primitives**,
**artifact-class compositions**, **route-level information
architecture**, **interactive states**, **locale-aware surfaces**, or
**accessibility audits**. Codifies the mechanical layer of
[`UX_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/Brand/UX Designer/canonicals/UX_DISCIPLINE.md)
(Wave M P5 mint per D-IH-86-BY; fulfils forward-charter D-IH-86-AX).

## When this rule applies

- Mint or modify a component primitive (any Shadcn-shape component
  under `boilerplate/components/` or `hlk-erp/components/`).
- Author or modify an artifact-class composition (page, modal,
  dialog, drawer, panel) under any consumer repo.
- Touch information architecture (navigation, breadcrumbs, sitemap,
  route hierarchy).
- Modify interaction states (loading / empty / error / success / disabled).
- Add or modify locale-aware surfaces (i18n translations, RTL layout,
  locale-specific brand voice).
- Conduct accessibility audit (axe-core, Lighthouse a11y, manual
  keyboard sweep, screen-reader review).

## RULE 1 — User-facing artefacts must satisfy the 7 UX dimensions (binding)

Every user-facing artefact (component primitive, artifact-class, route)
must pass the 7 UX dimensions defined in
[`UX_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/Brand/UX Designer/canonicals/UX_DISCIPLINE.md)
§2 before deploy:

- **UX-01** Research methods grounded in real personas → design-doc
  citation of PERSONA_REGISTRY rows + research evidence
- **UX-02** Per-channel design constraints → channel-tag frontmatter
  + per-channel checklist
- **UX-03** Accessibility bar (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum) → axe-core clean
  + Lighthouse a11y ≥ 95 + manual keyboard sweep
- **UX-04** Internationalisation strategy →
  `validate_locale_orthography.py` PASS per supported locale
- **UX-05** Information architecture → IA audit + 5-second test per
  persona
- **UX-06** Visual design quality →
  [`.cursor/skills/impeccable/SKILL.md`](../skills/impeccable/SKILL.md)
  checklist + design-token coverage audit
- **UX-07** Interaction patterns → per-component state inventory
  (loading + empty + error + success + disabled)

For internal-only surfaces (J-OP / J-AIC audience), the bar tightens
on UX-05 + UX-07 + UX-03 (keyboard) and lightens on UX-01 + UX-04 +
UX-06 (brand voice / locale).

## RULE 2 — Design system tokens are SSOT for visual properties (binding)

Hardcoded hex colour values, spacing values, border radius values,
font sizes, line heights, and z-index values are forbidden in
component primitives. All visual properties must derive from design
system tokens (Tailwind config + theme tokens). This is the UX-06
mechanical enforcement contract.

When a new visual property is needed, the mint follows: token first
(extend `tailwind.config.ts` + `theme.tokens.ts`), then component
consumes the token. PRs that introduce hardcoded values without a
corresponding token mint should fail review.

## RULE 3 — Every interactive component has explicit state coverage (binding)

Every interactive component (button, form input, modal trigger, etc.)
must define behaviour for at least: idle / hover / focus / active /
loading / disabled / error states. Composite components (forms, lists,
tables) additionally define: empty / partial / loaded / error states.

State omission is a UX-07 release-gate FAIL post-promotion. Pre-
promotion, it surfaces as INFO advisory in component review.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Code without user-facing surface (pure runtime infrastructure,
  background workers, CLI tools).
- Test fixtures or Storybook-only components used solely for
  development scaffolding.
- Internal session scratchwork or debugging notes.

